OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773252369
OL,3,C'Absolutely no faith' in Irish
OL,4,CGovernment providing answers in Omagh
OL,5,CInquiry
OL,7,FA woman whose brother was murdered in
OL,8,Fthe Omagh bomb has said that she has
OL,9,F"absolutely no faith" that the Irish
OL,10,FGovernment will help to provide
OL,11,Fanswers about the atrocity.
OL,13,FClaire Hayes has been speaking after
OL,14,Fthe Irish Government confirmed former
OL,15,Fministers and officials will be able
OL,16,Fto give evidence to the Omagh Inquiry
OL,17,Fin a court in Dublin.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
