OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773252369
OL,3,C'Absolutely no faith' in Irish
OL,4,CGovernment providing answers in Omagh
OL,5,CInquiry
OL,7,FOn Monday, the Irish Government
OL,8,Fconfirmed new legislation will allow
OL,9,Fformer ministers and state bodies to
OL,10,Fgive sworn testimony to the Omagh bomb
OL,11,Finquiry in courts in the Republic.
OL,13,FClaire Hayes welcomed the move, but
OL,14,Fsaid it's still not enough for her.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,447,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F446A1773252369
OL,3,C'Absolutely no faith' in Irish
OL,4,CGovernment providing answers in Omagh
OL,5,CInquiry
OL,7,FShe said: "I have absolutely no faith
OL,8,Fin the Irish Government. None
OL,9,Fwhatsoever. And that's from a personal
OL,10,Fstandpoint. There has been too much.
OL,11,FToo much hurt. Too much of, 'We can't
OL,12,Ftouch that,' 'We can't go there.' Why
OL,13,Fcan't you go there? What is it that
OL,14,Fyou're sitting on?"
OL,16,FOn a visit to Belfast on Monday, the
OL,17,FIrish Foreign Affairs Minister Helen
OL,18,FMcEntee said the Irish Government
OL,19,Fwould consider if it needs to do more
OL,20,Fon the Omagh Bombing Inquiry.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/10
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
